						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, [Rājarāja I] = 985-1014 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>In Grantha and Sanskrit. Later part broken. Mentions something (details lost) done by a Chōḻa feudatory named Parāntakap-pallavaraiyaṉ of Naṭār in Umbaḷa-nāḍu, son of Mumuṭichōḻa-Umpaḷa-nāṭṭu-Mūvēntavēḷān, and grandson of Chempiyaṉ-Umpaḷa-nāṭṭu-Mūvēntavēḷāṉ. He was a favourite of King Rājarāja.</p>						

						</summary>
